  "intent_precise": "Combo IC: Using dmso_res (reservoir, slot 1), compound_plate (pcr_plate, slot 2), hdpf1 (pcr_plate, slot 4), hdpf2 (pcr_plate, slot 5). (1) Transfer from source A1 to destination A1. (2) Distribute from source A1 to vsp wells A1-G1 (5 wells). (3) Transfer from compound_plate (A1-B1 (5 wells)) to vsp (A1-G1 (5 wells)). (4) Mix 5 times at 100\u00b5L in vsp A1. (5) Transfer from source A1 to destination A1. (6) Mix 5 times at 100\u00b5L. (7) Transfer from source A1 to vsp A12. (8) Mix 5 times at 100\u00b5L in vsp A12. (9) Transfer from source A1 to destination A1. (10) Mix 5 times at 100\u00b5L. (11) Transfer from source A1 to hsp A1. (12) Mix 5 times at 100\u00b5L in hsp A1. (13) Transfer from source A1 to destination A1. (14) Mix 5 times at 100\u00b5L. (15) Transfer from source A1 to hsp H1. (16) Mix 5 times at 100\u00b5L in hsp H1. (17) Transfer from source A1 to destination A1. (18) Mix 5 times at 100\u00b5L. (19) Distribute from source A1 to destination wells A1-A1 (4 wells).",
  "intent_concise": "Perform 2 distribution steps. (using 100\u00b5L)",
  "intent": "For the Combo IC protocol, start by setting up your workspace with the DMSO reservoir in slot 1, compound plate in slot 2, and the hdpf1 and hdpf2 PCR plates in slots 4 and 5 respectively. Begin by transferring from source A1 to destination A1, then distribute from that same source A1 to VSP wells A1 through G1 (5 wells total), followed by transferring compounds from the compound plate wells A1-B1 (5 wells) to the corresponding VSP wells A1-G1, and mix 5 times at 100\u00b5L in VSP A1. Continue with the sequential A1 to A1 transfers, mixing 5 times at 100\u00b5L after each step, but note the specific destination changes: transfer to VSP A12 (mix in A12), then to HSP A1 (mix in A1), then to HSP H1 (mix in H1), and finally distribute from source A1 to destination wells A1-A1 across 4 wells. Remember to maintain the 5x mixing at 100\u00b5L volume at each specified well location throughout the entire protocol.",
